Abertis to Bid for Spain Airports with CVC, AXA, Expansion Says

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-08-15T05:31:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/abertis-to-bid-for-spain-airports-with-cvc-axa-expansion-says.html
Abertis Infraestructuras SA (ABE)  will bid
for concessions to run  Spain ’s Madrid and Barcelona airports in
conjunction with CVC Capital Partners Ltd. and  Axa SA (CS) ,  Expansion 
reported, citing unidentified people with knowledge of the
matter.  Bidders for the contracts will have to make initial payment
of 3.7 billion euros ($5.3 billion) for Madrid’s Barajas airport
and 1.6 billion euros for Barcelona’s El Prat, the newspaper
said, citing information published in July by state-owned
airport operator Aena Aeropuertos SA.  The winner of the contracts will have to cede 20 percent of
the airport’s revenue to Aena, which currently runs both hubs,
the newspaper added.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net  